description:
The settings.rs file has a compilation error that prevents the entire agui-desktop crate from building.

ERROR:
error[E0382]: use of moved value: `on_close`
  --> crates/agui-desktop/src/settings.rs:492:93
   |
179 |     on_close: impl Fn(&mut V, &mut Window, &mut Context<V>) + 'static,
    |     -------- move occurs because `on_close` has type `impl Fn(...)`, which does not implement the `Copy` trait
...
284 |                                     on_close(view, window, cx);
    |                                     -------- variable moved due to use in closure
...
492 |                                         .on_mouse_down(gpui::MouseButton::Left, cx.listener(move |view, _, window, cx| {
    |                                                                                             ^^ value used here after move
493 |                                             on_close(view, window, cx);
    |                                             -------- use occurs due to use in closure

LOCATION:
- crates/agui-desktop/src/settings.rs:179 (function signature)
- Lines 284 and 493 (two uses of on_close closure)

CAUSE:
The on_close closure is moved into two different cx.listener closures, but it doesn't implement Clone or Copy. After the first move (line 284), it's no longer available for the second use (line 493).

SOLUTION OPTIONS:
1. Wrap on_close in Arc to allow multiple ownership
2. Add Clone bound to on_close parameter: `on_close: impl Fn(...) + Clone + 'static`
3. Clone the closure before each use (requires Clone bound)

RECOMMENDED FIX:
Add Clone bound to the on_close parameter:

```rust
pub fn render_settings_dialog<V: 'static>(
    state: &SettingsState,
    on_close: impl Fn(&mut V, &mut Window, &mut Context<V>) + Clone + 'static,
    // ... rest of parameters
) -> gpui::Div {
    // ...
    // First use
    .on_mouse_down(gpui::MouseButton::Left, cx.listener({
        let on_close = on_close.clone();
        move |view, _, window, cx| {
            on_close(view, window, cx);
        }
    }))
    // ...
    // Second use
    .on_mouse_down(gpui::MouseButton::Left, cx.listener({
        let on_close = on_close.clone();
        move |view, _, window, cx| {
            on_close(view, window, cx);
        }
    }))
}
```

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
- [ ] agui-desktop builds without errors
- [ ] Settings dialog renders correctly
- [ ] Close button (X) works
- [ ] Escape key to close works (if applicable)

PRIORITY: P1 (blocks all other development on agui-desktop)
